	   <tr><td colspan=2>The big deal is this... the spell: Invoke Fear costs 100 mana and has a 7 second recovery time.&nbsp;&nbsp;The casting time on this staff is approximately 3-3.5 seconds.  So to start off with, it casts Invoke Fear faster than you can using the conventional method, so that puts the casting speed issue to rest.  As far as losing mana by equipping a 2hb, you actually spend far less mana on fears than you lose from not holding two hand items.. and in fact you recieve a net mana GAIN, given you are fear kiting.  If you aren't using fear, stow this staff in a bag and hold your int/mana items.  This staff would be great for a necro who solos a lot, I can just imagine how awesome it is.  I had one of these staves at one time and sold it to a necro who I got to know better, he still uses and loves it, groups love him (in outdoor zone) because he can fear the mob over and over and not worry about mana.  If you're a necro that does a good bit of fear kiting, this staff is your BOON.  Get one.  That is all.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
