	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9823121986774><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=485&mid=9823121986774>Got it - 4th Xlagoz</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=485&mid=9823121986774#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Feb 16th 3:29 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Here's how I did it - I was 51 at the time.<br>1) Go invis and make your way down past the spiders.<br>2) Go invis to undead and make your way down past the skeletons/ghosts.<br>3) When you get to the church, go in and select Xalgoz (or PH), then keep him selected and run out of the church to the safe spot directly behind where Xalgoz is. Its a little open area and nothing spawns or wanders there.<br>4) Summon pet, make sure you keep Xalgoz selected.<br>5) Med to full.<br>6) Cast your highest undead DD on Xalgoz and it will pull him single, all the way around to you. By that time you can usually cast 2 or 3 of the DD's on him (this will only work if all the other mobs are green to you, I was level 51, so I would suggest being at least that).<br>7) Kill him. Its a pretty easy kill with a pet.<br>8) Wait 30 minutes, reinvis to undead, go in and select him, go back, summon pet, rinse, repeat. I got a Blade of Xalgoz the first kill, a PH the 2nd kill, a Xalgozian Fang the 3rd time, the Staff the 4th time. As you can imagine, Im pretty happy about that. :)<br><br>Nunya Nocturne &lt;Burnt Offerings&gt;<br>Level 53 Heretic<br>Rodcet Nife<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
